I decided to have this be the exception that proves the rule, as it were. (And I looked up that expression.) If there's anything that would unnerve an O5, I believe it would be an uncontainable SCP with infinite power. I wrote those two comments in a bit of a hurry: if you think they need a bit of rewording (O5-2 is a little hysterical in his use of formatting) then go ahead. IIRC, O5s have used extremely informal language in the past: I thought this was the norm.

I believe the English parlour and hamburger are both essential to 343: he is completely and utterly benign, or at least that's all he chooses to show us.

What I did was remove all traces of him not being so benign, so that all we have are suspicions. We can't even process the idea of an SCP with that much power that isn't a threat, and for good reason, considering all the harmful stuff we have. So we watch him very, very, carefully, and pray that he's only what he appears to be.

If we're to have an SCP that's may or not be God, then I think this is the only way we can really swing it.







